descCRN['10536&TermDescription=Fall%202017'] = '<p>Notes:<br />*Cross-listed with PHYS 340-01; *ACTC students may register on April 28th with permission of instructor*<br/>A survey of fundamental ideas and methods used in the design and construction of digital electronic circuits such as computers. Emphasis will be on applying the theoretical aspects of digital design to the actual construction of circuits in the laboratory. Topics to be covered include basic circuit theory, transistor physics, logic families (TTL, CMOS), Boolean logic principles, combinatorial design techniques, sequential logic techniques, memory circuits and timing, and applications to microprocessor and computer design. Three lectures and one three-hour laboratory per week. (4 credits) <br/></p>';
